When we create string without new operator it will exist previous string and if you create another string it will print
result true.
Example :-
     String a = "Hello World";
     String b = "Hello World";
if we compare both string like if(a==b), It will print result true.

But When we create string with new operator it will create string in object form because new create always creates object
so address will be changed and it will be stored in heap memory so if we compare both string it will print result false.

Example :-
      String x = "Hello World";
      String y = new String ("Hello World");
if we compare both string like if (x==y), It will print result false;